If you need to upgrade a server running Windows Server 2008 R2 Standard to either the Enterprise, or Datacenter editions, it’s possible to do so online, without re-installing Windows.

Open an elevated command prompt and type following command to get current Windows version


```
DISM /Online /Get-CurrentEdition
```

Use following command to list upgrade options.

```
DISM /Online /Get-TargetEditions

Use following command to upgrade your version of Windows Server. You can also upgrade to DataCenter Edition in similar way. You need to have a key for Enterprise edition and fill in the XXXX with that information, key is available in google sheet. Once the command is done running you will need to restart your computer, if you are ready just type “Y”.

```
DISM /Online /Set-Edition:ServerEnterprise /ProductKey:xxxxxx
